<section>
<title>Detailed Description</title>

<para>The base class for all hand models, both graphics and physics.</para>

<para>This class serves as the interface between the HandController object and the concrete hand object containing the graphics and physics of a hand.</para>

<para>Subclasses of <link linkend="_class_leap_1_1_unity_1_1_hand_model">HandModel</link> must implement <link linkend="_class_leap_1_1_unity_1_1_hand_model_1a67f1a6887e0803c96095a376fc1e6031">InitHand()</link> and <link linkend="_class_leap_1_1_unity_1_1_hand_model_1acbb96fd18f28d01a74c1e0ac709b1977">UpdateHand()</link>. The <link linkend="_class_leap_1_1_unity_1_1_hand_model_1acbb96fd18f28d01a74c1e0ac709b1977">UpdateHand()</link> function is called in the <link linkend="_namespace_leap_1_1_unity">Unity</link> Update() phase for graphics <link linkend="_class_leap_1_1_unity_1_1_hand_model">HandModel</link> instances; and in the <link linkend="_namespace_leap_1_1_unity">Unity</link> FixedUpdate() phase for physics objects. <link linkend="_class_leap_1_1_unity_1_1_hand_model_1a67f1a6887e0803c96095a376fc1e6031">InitHand()</link> is called once, when the hand is created and is followed by a call to <link linkend="_class_leap_1_1_unity_1_1_hand_model_1acbb96fd18f28d01a74c1e0ac709b1977">UpdateHand()</link>. </para>
